Description: Fragment of flattened handle at neck join from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Nikephoros. Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 181, 33.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0124)
